data.description: Introducing Cosmopolitan's #1 Rated Thermal Legging, and your new go-to winter legging with the perfect balance of tech and fashion. The design lends its self to be easily dressed up or dressed down for ultimate styling versatility. Plus it has not one but two phone pockets for hands free life on the go. Our Amy Winter Thermal Phone Pocket Tech legging has also been designed with a gusset. This triangular panel of fabric sewn into the crotch (gusset) prevents the leggings from 'riding up' (no camel toe) and provides more flexibility and freedom of movement. The thermal lining also gives a more compressive feel when worn. If you would prefer a more relaxed fit for all day wear we suggest you go up a size. If you prefer a more snug and firm fit, we suggest your usual size. PLEASE NOTE: Due to the nature of brushed fleece, these leggings can be prone to pilling so we recommend washing yours inside out in our Active Washbag on a delicate cycle to extend it's life. If you do not own a garment bag, a gentle hand wash is recommended.

data.title: USDA - National Agricultural Statistics Service - Census of Agriculture
data.description: The Census of Agriculture is a complete count of U.S. farms and ranches and the people who operate them. Even small plots of land - whether rural or urban - growing fruit, vegetables or some food animals count if $1,000 or more of such products were raised and sold, or normally would have been sold, during the Census year. The Census of Agriculture, taken only once every five years, looks at land use and ownership, operator characteristics, production practices, income and expenditures. For America's farmers and ranchers, the Census of Agriculture is their voice, their future, and their opportunity.
